  "prompt": "How would you word \"damas\" and \"chambelanes\" for an english Quinceanera invitation?",
  "response": "For an English Quincea\u00f1era invitation, you can use the following terms:\n\n- \"Damas\" can be translated to \"Bridesmaids\" or \"Court of Honor\".\n- \"Chambelanes\" can be translated to \"Escorts\" or \"Honor Attendants\".\n\nYou could phrase it like this:\n\n\"Join us in celebrating [Name]'s Quincea\u00f1era with her Court of Honor and Escorts.\"\n\nThis wording conveys the spirit of the traditional roles while making it accessible to an English-speaking audience.",
